## 6. Value Proposition
- Accelerates R&D and reduces costs
- Democratizes access to advanced nanomedicine design tools
- Supports education, training, and workforce development
- Enables safe, responsible, and regulatory-ready innovation

## 7. Example Workflow
1. User designs a nanoparticle by adjusting size, charge, ligands, and payload
2. Matches design to a biological target (e.g., tumor, blood, cell type)
3. Simulates drug delivery and visualizes PK/PD curves
4. Assesses safety and toxicity risk
5. Estimates cost and feasibility
6. Generates experimental protocol and professional report

## 8. Use Cases
- Academic research and teaching
- Pharmaceutical R&D
- Regulatory and safety assessment
- Investment due diligence
- Government health-tech initiatives

